gomodel:SYNGO_1103  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: In this study, Cole et al report on the genetic disruption of ZnT-3 gene in mice (see Fig. 1 B and C for the verification). The authors perform immunocytochemistry for detection of ZnT-3 protein using a polyclonal antibody (immuno-EM) on the SVs in mossy fiber terminals in hippocampus (Fig. 5). The specificity of the immunodetection is verified by staining for ZnT-3 in WT, +/- and KO animals.. Experimental description: MATERIALS AND METHODS\nGeneration of ZnT3 Knockout Mice. After isolating the\nZnT3 gene from a 129Sv mouse genomic library (16), a\ntargeting vector was constructed by replacing a 4.3-kb StuI-\nAflII fragment encoding the first four exons with a cassette\ncontaining nuclear lacZ (nlacZ) and a neomycin-resistance\ngene (neor) driven by the polII promoter." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1103" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

